ğŸš€ Minikube Installation on Amazon Linux 2023

This guide explains how to install Minikube on Amazon Linux 2023 using the Docker driver.
All steps are tested and suitable for learning and practice.

ğŸ“Œ Prerequisites

Amazon Linux 2023 EC2 instance

User: ec2-user

Architecture: x86_64

Internet access

IAM role or security group allowing outbound access

ğŸ§± Step 1: Update the System
sudo dnf update -y

ğŸ“¦ Step 2: Install Required Dependencies
sudo dnf install -y curl wget conntrack socat iptables iproute-tc


These packages are required for Kubernetes networking and container runtime support.

ğŸ³ Step 3: Install Docker (Amazon Linux 2023 Method)

âš ï¸ Docker convenience script (get.docker.com) is not supported on Amazon Linux 2023.

Install Docker
sudo dnf install -y docker

Start and Enable Docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker

ğŸ‘¤ Step 4: Configure Docker Access for ec2-user (Critical)
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user
newgrp docker

Verify Docker (No sudo)
docker ps
docker version

â˜¸ï¸ Step 5: Install Minikube
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

Verify Installation
minikube version

ğŸ§° Step 6: Install kubectl
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -Ls https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/

Verify kubectl
kubectl version --client

â–¶ï¸ Step 7: Start Minikube (Do NOT use sudo)
minikube start --driver=docker

âœ… Step 8: Verify Kubernetes Cluster
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods -A


Expected:

Node status: Ready

Core system pods: Running

ğŸŒ Accessing Services on EC2 (Important)
NodePort Limitation

NodePort services are not directly accessible via EC2 public IP when using Minikube with Docker.

Recommended Options
Option 1: Minikube Service URL
minikube service <service-name> --url

Option 2: Port Forwarding
kubectl port-forward svc/<service-name> 8080:80


Access in browser:

http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:8080

âŒ Common Mistakes to Avoid

Running minikube with sudo

Using Docker convenience install script

Forgetting to add user to docker group

Expecting NodePort to behave like EKS

Using VM drivers on EC2

ğŸ§  Key Takeaway

Amazon Linux 2023 requires Docker installation via Amazon repositories.
Minikube must run as a non-root user with Docker group access.